151
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,910
of the primary personality.

152
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,360
But she was an exception.

153
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,200
Super dangerous.

154
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,620
Not without benefits though.

155
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,360
She helped us

156
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:59,510
expel those other alters.

157
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:03,840
How nice.

158
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:11,750
[Jia Xiaoduo (Female, 25), 09.30, Libra]

159
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:08,620
[Escape Room NPC Manager]

160
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:14,120
Jia Xiaoduo expelled the other alters

161
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:17,200
to clear the obstacles around you
to find you.

162
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,870
Just like a bird,

163
00:16:20,870 --> 00:16:24,330
focused on clearing the surrounding
dead branches and weeds,

164
00:16:24,670 --> 00:16:28,440
but actually intending to search
for something else in the distance.

165
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,240
She was in your spiritual world,

166
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,010
looking for you.

167
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:37,890
That's so exhausting.

168
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:49,390
And it's futile.

169
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,870
When she is in your world,

170
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,480
you aren't there.

171
00:16:54,540 --> 00:16:57,580
[Jia Xiaoduo]

172
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:00,510
When you are in this world,

173
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,790
she isn't here.

174
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:10,880
[Assessment Form: Jia Xiaoduo]

175
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:12,640
We have never met before.

176
00:17:13,589 --> 00:17:15,849
Alters never meet
the primary identity,

177
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:17,480
even in

178
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,510
a virtual world.

179
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,420
In principle, they won't.

180
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,640
In principle?

181
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:31,350
In principle,

182
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:34,070
they won't.

183
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:41,540
[Assessment Form: Jia Xiaoduo]

184
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:42,880
That's good.

185
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,240
What if...

186
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:01,880
And I mean, if...

187
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:06,680
What if she replaces me?

188
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:09,790
Almost.

189
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,730
If she really replaced you,

190
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,860
you'd still look like you,

191
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,550
but your soul

192
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,000
would be hers.

193
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,760
But she still wouldn't find you.

194
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:33,880
Almost?

195
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:36,890
What do you mean?

196
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:51,310
I asked her a question before.

197
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,000
I once asked her to choose

198
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,200
between her and you,

199
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:00,790
where one of you

200
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:04,350
has to disappear.

201
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,880
She chose herself.

202
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,550
Alters think like that too?

203
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,270
She believes

204
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:43,870
she is the primary identity.

205
00:19:47,590 --> 00:19:48,510
Dr. Shi.

206
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,410
It's past his medication time.

207
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,450
Almost done.

208
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:56,200
I'm glad you cured me.

209
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,240
Thank you.

210
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,480
Your phone.

211
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:03,920
There are some contacts in here

212
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,000
you no longer need.

213
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:06,270
Want me to help you

214
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,400
delete them?

215
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:09,240
Like whom?

216
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:11,790
Yourself.

217
00:20:13,790 --> 00:20:15,320
It's saved under my number.

218
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:17,720
You even called me before.

219
00:20:17,790 --> 00:20:18,440
Remember?

220
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:25,100
[Ride-Hailing Driver Xu]

221
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:27,160
[Delete]

222
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,690
You'll be discharged soon.

223
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:32,160
Should I notify your sister
to pick you up?

224
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:38,400
Please do.

225
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:39,790
Okay.

226
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,240
Prepare his meds.

227
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,680
A month's supply.

228
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:45,680
Okay.

229
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,440
Thank you.

230
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,680
Is he cured?

231
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:13,590
Tell him to

232
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,160
come back for a refill

233
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,200
when his meds run out.

234
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:20,240
But this morning,

235
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:22,510
he was still Jia Xiaoduo.

236
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:26,600
Jia Xiaoduo is still there.

237
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:28,590
He should know it too.

238
00:21:29,270 --> 00:21:30,590
Can he know?

239
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:33,790
For DID patients,

240
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:35,510
not usually.

241
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,070
But with mental illnesses,

242
00:21:38,070 --> 00:21:39,000
it's hard to say.

243
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:40,030
Who knows?

244
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,330
I think it's quite nice.

245
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:44,400
Is it?

246
00:21:46,030 --> 00:21:48,110
A woman living in his heart,

247
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:50,570
impossible to forget even if he wants to.

248
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:53,000
But in the real world,

249
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,550
they'll never meet.

250
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,590
Never?

251
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:00,680
Never.

252
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:35,100
I'll leave the door unlocked.

253
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:36,440
Why?

254
00:23:37,070 --> 00:23:39,030
Dr. Shi just called your sister.

255
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,290
She'll be here soon.

256
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:44,830
The pipe under the sink is leaking.

257
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:48,730
We'll fix it once you leave.

258
00:24:18,140 --> 00:24:19,660
[Weekly workout plan]

259
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:30,380
[The Minds of Billy Milligan]

260
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:35,880
Xu Tian.

261
00:26:36,270 --> 00:26:37,800
Meds prescribed by Dr. Shi.

262
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:38,830
A month's supply.

263
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:19,510
I like someone.

264
00:28:24,030 --> 00:28:25,400
She likes me too.

265
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:29,920
But she

266
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:31,880
doesn't exist.

267
00:28:38,750 --> 00:28:40,920
She has never existed.

268
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:48,200
How is this possible?

269
00:28:53,590 --> 00:28:55,960
People come and go in this world,

270
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:59,400
all hurried yet joyful.

271
00:29:01,070 --> 00:29:03,160
How can I stay calm?

272
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,550
She must be

273
00:29:08,270 --> 00:29:09,960
somewhere.

274
00:29:13,750 --> 00:29:15,590
How can I find her

275
00:29:17,030 --> 00:29:18,230
in this mortal world?

276
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:05,400
Tian.

277
00:30:08,030 --> 00:30:09,760
I'm leaving tomorrow morning.

278
00:30:10,070 --> 00:30:11,670
So I came to pick you up today.

279
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:16,250
Not asking where I'm going?

280
00:30:19,510 --> 00:30:20,440
Back to Dangkou?

281
00:30:22,310 --> 00:30:23,000
No.

282
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:25,350
I've never gone back

283
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,660
since Mom passed away in 2010.

284
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,240
Have you?

285
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:32,790
I don't think so.

286
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,930
Don't you care where I'm going?

287
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,300
Wherever it is, it's far away, right?

288
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:56,160
Why are you being so cruel?

289
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:01,400
It has nothing to do with being cruel.

290
00:31:06,070 --> 00:31:08,870
I'm always the one
sending you to and picking you up

291
